#!/usr/bin/env python3
# ============================================================================
#  QATS — Advanced Predictive ML Engine  v2.0
#  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Models used (NO simple linear/logistic regression):
#
#  1. LINE RISK — RandomForestClassifier  (3-class: Low / Medium / High risk)
#     Features: 12 engineered features per line per week
#       rolling-4w NG mean, rolling std, exponential-weighted trend,
#       CTQ NG rate, open NC count, pass-rate slope, audit frequency,
#       inter-week NG variance, max single-week NG, severity score,
#       days since last high-risk event, model-change flag
#     Fallback: ExtraTreesClassifier if <30 samples
#     Outputs: class + probability distribution + feature importances
#
#  2. NC FORECAST — Holt-Winters Exponential Smoothing  (trend + season)
#     Seasonal period = 4 weeks (monthly manufacturing cycle)
#     Falls back to SARIMA-lite (manual AR(1) + seasonal diff) if < 8 weeks
#     Confidence bands: 80% and 95% via residual bootstrap
#     Metric: MAPE on hold-out (last 2 weeks)
#
#  3. PARAMETER FAILURE RISK — RandomForestClassifier per parameter
#     Binary: will this param fail next week? (1 = NG expected)
#     Features: recent NG rate, rolling 4w std, CTQ flag, stage risk,
#       line risk, consecutive NG streak, days since last NG
#     Trained on sliding-window labels: next-week NG = 1 or 0
#     Outputs: probability 0-1, reason phrase
#
#  4. ANOMALY DETECTION — Isolation Forest
#     Detects audits that are statistical outliers in their line context
#     (e.g. sudden spike in NG on a normally clean line)
#     Outputs: anomaly score, anomalous audit list
#
#  5. SHIFT / OPERATOR / MODEL RISK MATRIX
#     Chi-square association test (not regression) of shift/operator/model
#     with NG incidence. Outputs top risk combinations.
#
#  Run:   python predict.py
#  Needs: pip install pymysql numpy pandas scikit-learn statsmodels
# ============================================================================

